# Android Architecture Rules

## Core Principle: Decoupling Over Everything

Features communicate through `-api` modules only. An `-impl` module must never depend on another `-impl` module. If two features need to interact, one exposes an interface in its `-api`, the other injects it. This is non-negotiable ŌĆö it prevents circular dependencies and keeps the Dagger graph clean.

---

## Module Structure

Every feature follows the `-api` / `-impl` split:

```
my-feature/
  my-feature-api/       ŌåÉ interfaces, data classes, no implementation
  my-feature-impl/      ŌåÉ implementation, UI, DI bindings
```

Rules:
- `my-feature-impl` depends on `my-feature-api`
- `my-feature-impl` depends on other features' `-api` modules only ŌĆö never their `-impl`
- `settings.gradle` auto-discovers modules 2 levels deep ŌĆö no manual `include` needed
- New `-impl` modules must be added to `app/build.gradle` to enter the Dagger graph
- UI resources (layouts, drawables, strings) live inside the `-impl` module, not a separate UI module
- String resource files are named by feature: `strings-my-feature.xml` (not `strings.xml`)

